The paper focuses on developing a novel artificial neural network model for image classification that is robust against adversarial attacks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of attention mechanisms and recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the properties of the animal visual system, which suggests that it may belong to the neuroscience and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses techniques such as SPSA and PGD, which are commonly used in adversarial machine learning (cs.AI) sub-category.
